    "title": "Reading and literacy – a joint approach across education and culture",
    "link": "https://culture.ec.europa.eu/whats-new/news/reading-and-literacy-a-joint-approach-across-education-and-culture",
    "pubDate": "2026-05-07T12:18:57.000Z",
    "content": "<html><head></head><body><h1 class=\"title-h1 eac-page-title\">Reading and literacy – a joint approach across education and culture</h1>\n<span><span>csudaga</span></span>\n<span><time datetime=\"2026-05-07T14:18:57+02:00\" title=\"Thursday, May 7, 2026 - 14:18\">Thu, 05/07/2026 - 14:18</time>\n</span>\n<div class=\"ecl\"><p>The Literacy for Democracy conference gathered over 200 participants in Warsaw. It emphasised the human dimension of reading, highlighting that literacy skills are central to addressing Europe’s current challenges, including competitiveness and democracy.</p><h2>Supporting parents as influencers of young minds</h2><p>The conference brought together policymakers, reading promotion specialists, paediatricians, book sector and business community representatives. They shared experiences and discussed key issues, such as how to support parents and caregivers in their role as influencers of young minds, and the policy measures already in place as well as potential areas for enhancement.</p><h2>Preparing the foundations of the EU Literacy Coalition</h2><p>A two half-day workshop followed the conference to prepare the foundations of the EU Literacy Coalition, that will be established in autumn 2026 as par</p></div></body></html>",
