    "pubDate": "2026-04-23T12:25:21.000Z",
    "content": "<html><head></head><body><h1 class=\"title-h1 eac-page-title\">European Heritage Label: 13 new sites celebrated in Brussels</h1>\n<span><span>csudaga</span></span>\n<span><time datetime=\"2026-04-23T14:25:21+02:00\" title=\"Thursday, April 23, 2026 - 14:25\">Thu, 04/23/2026 - 14:25</time>\n</span>\n<div class=\"ecl\"><h2>Recognition of new sites at the ceremony</h2><p>Marking the culmination of the 2025 selection process, the European Heritage Label (EHL) ceremony took place at the Art and History Museum in Brussels. The heritage community gathered to recognise <a href=\"https://culture.ec.europa.eu/whats-new/news/13-sites-to-receive-the-european-heritage-label?\">the 13 newly awarded sites</a>.</p><p>The event brought together EHL national coordinators and sites, representatives from European institutions, cultural heritage experts, stakeholders and members of the European Parliament. The ceremony featured performances by participating sites, highlighting the diversity of Europe’s heritage and its role in promoting shared values.</p><p>European Commissioner for Intergenerational Fairness, Youth, Culture and Sport, Glenn Micallef opened the ceremony.&nbsp;<br>Bogdan Andrzej Zdrojewski, Vice Chair of the Committee on Cul</p></div></body></html>",
